column5: Any reports for walleye, musky, bass in the area? Heading up next week.Thanks in advance Sent from my iPhone using Tapatalk Pro

Bass has been good, seeing lots of nice muskie pics from Wylie Point Lodge on Social media, walleye around but not all centred on humps. We have caught walleye in all depths of water, 2-3 to 30'. the shallow one's caught on little 2.75" swimbaits casting held on 1/6oz zman ned rig jigs.
Last year I went in July and couldn't catch a walleye over 20Â”. I hope the bigger ones are biting. Thanks!Sent from my iPhone using Tapatalk Pro
